Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Roughly chop the @mushrooms{250%grams}.

Halve and peel the @onion{1}. Cut each half into 3 wedges.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Roughly chop the @parsley{5%grams} (stalks and all).

Place a #pot{} over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Fry the onion, garlic and mushrooms until softened, stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Lower heat to medium-high. Add the @BBQ rub{1%sachet} and @flour{1%tbsp} (double for 4p). Fry for ~{1%minute}.

Shake the @coconut milk{1%pack} and reserve 1 tbsp (double for 4p). Add remaining coconut milk, @Hello Muscat{1%sachet}, half the chopped parsley and @water{250%ml} (double for 4p) to the pot.

Bring to a boil, then cover and simmer for ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, cut the @baguette{2} widthways at an angle into 2cm slices.

Lay the slices on a #baking tray{}. Bake until golden brown, ~{8-10%minutes}.

While the crostini are crisping, use a #fork{} to mash together the @Greek style cheese{100%grams} and reserved coconut milk. You want to make a sort of paste!

Once the crostinis are crispy, spread the cheese mixture on top of each slice.

Garnish with a crack of @black pepper{to taste}.

Season the stew to taste with @salt{to taste} and pepper.

Divide between #bowls{}.

Garnish with a sprinkling of remaining parsley.

Serve the Greek style cheese crostini alongside.